2. Nf3
{ It is useful to include this move before committing to d3 or g3. Please note that the resulting position can be also reached via the 1. Nf3 c5 2. e4 move order. }
2... Nc6
{ In this chapter we will take a look at Black's lines connected with 2... Nc6 and 2... d6. After 2... e6 I will recommend a specific setup connected with a quick Qe2. You can check my analysis of that line in the next chapter. I want to mention that lines with 2... g6 will transpose to either 2... d6 or 2... Nc6 - or even sometimes to the lines with ...e6 ...d5 and ...Nge7/...Nf6 from the previous chapter. I didn't analyse variations such as 2... a6 or 2... Nf6 - you can use the same setup against all of them and they will transpose one to another sooner or later. }
