Bc7 9. c3 d4 { I think this is an inaccuracy. } 10. Nb3
{ Putting pressure on Black's centre is always nice ! } 10... Bb6
{ 10... b6 was analysed in the theoretical section. } 11. e5
{ Opening up the g2-Bishop and securing a space advantage. } 11... Na5 12. Ng5
{ This excellent move combines attacking ideas on the kingside with a positional plan Ng5-e4-d6 }
12... Nxb3 13. axb3 Nf5 14. Be4
{ Improving the Bishop is quite thematic but in this case, I would prefer to stick to Ne4 ideas maybe followed by Bg5 - not forgetting about Qh5. }
14... f6
{ I think that Black should play 14... h6, even if it looks suicidal. He would win some time by expelling our Knight and should organize his defence on time. }
