Rf3 31. Qh4 Rc2 32. Rad1 { Preparing a nasty surprise on the back rank. } 32...
Qd5
{ It is tough to believe that it was a game continuation but I see that every source gives 32... Qd5 as a move that actually was played. }
33. Ne3
{ White was never in any danger and he kept his big advantage from the start to the end. You should be very happy if your opponent castles into the fire with ...O-O-O. }
