{ It was not too late to spoil everything.   37.Bg2 ?  would be bad due to  37...Rb1+  38.Kh2  Rb2 !  and White can't protect the f-pawn without allowing a repeat of moves.   Also,  37.Bf3 ?  would be inaccurate due to  37...Bxh3  38.Rxh7  and Black has  38...Rxf6 !  attacking the Bishop. In both cases, it would lead to a draw. You need to be precise everywhere. A position that looks completely winning can be spoiled by one stupid move. }
