{ I like this flexible move. Normally White starts with 6. Nbd2 but I can imagine that my Knight can sometimes go to a3 or even c3. In this kinds of positions, it is very useful to make moves that we are 100% sure we will do such as O-O or e4, but such continuations as Re1 c3 or Nbd2 may be useful or not - it depends on our opponent's plan. }
6... Nge7 7. c3 O-O 8. a3
